<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF9CE537D6F0FD45D48447F2" blockId="8.[144,759,659,926]" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF9CE537D6F0FD45D40C46C5" box="[144,262,660,681]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Distinguished from all congeners, except 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF9CE537D6F0FD63D43646AB" baseAuthorityName="Costa, Lacerda &amp; Tanizaki" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[144,316,690,711]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="155" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="citrinipinnis">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF9CE537D6F0FD63D43646AB" box="[144,316,690,711]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">L. citrinipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in having dorsal-fin origin in vertical between base of seventh and ninth anal-fin rays (vs. between base of second and sixth anal-fin rays). It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF9CE537D726FCDFD4F8474F" baseAuthorityName="Costa, Lacerda &amp; Tanizaki" baseAuthorityYear="1988" box="[326,498,782,803]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="155" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="citrinipinnis">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF9CE537D726FCDFD4F8474F" box="[326,498,782,803]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">L. citrinipinnis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having caudal fin lanceolate (vs. elliptical), dark-red stripe on distal margin of dorsal and anal fins, and dorsal and ventral margin of caudal fin in males (vs. reddish brown pigmentation diffuse).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF9CE537D6F0FC17D7D047B0" blockId="8.[144,730,966,988]" box="[144,730,966,988]" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF9CE537D6F0FC17D5F147B7" box="[144,251,966,987]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Remarks:</emphasis>
Redescribed by Costa &amp; Lacerda (1988).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF9CE537D6F0FBD4D4D44034" blockId="8.[144,759,1029,1112]" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF9CE537D6F0FBD4D42B4076" box="[144,289,1029,1050]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Distribution:</emphasis>
Estrela and Iguaçu river basins, both draining into Guanabara bay, 
<collectingRegion id="49BEF802FF9CE537D79CFBF2D7F84055" box="[508,754,1059,1081]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Rio de Janeiro state</collectingRegion>
, south-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F36D7670FF9CE537D756FB93D4764034" box="[310,380,1090,1112]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="13412A65FF9CE537D7EEFB93D4DA4034" box="[398,464,1090,1112]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="4.[144,223,1853,1872]" captionTargetBox="[368,1198,1236,1823]" captionTargetId="figure-333@4.[367,1199,1235,1824]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 5. Geographical distribution of Leptolebias in Rio de Janeiro state, south-eastern Brazil: 1, L. marmoratus, L. splendens, and L. opalescens; 2, L. marmoratus and L. opalescens; 3, L. splendens; 4, L. citrinipinnis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4634949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4634949/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC536E0FF9CE537D6F0FB51D7A24143" blockId="8.[144,759,1152,1327]" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF9CE537D6F0FB51D4BD40FA" box="[144,439,1152,1174]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Habitat and conservation:</emphasis>
Not collected since 1981, so possibly extinct. Its area of occurrence was formerly occupied by dense rainforest, but is now highly urbanized. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF9CE537D6B5FB0DD4D6409D" baseAuthorityName="Myers" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[213,476,1244,1265]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="155" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="opalescens">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF9CE537D6B5FB0DD4D6409D" box="[213,476,1244,1265]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">Leptolebias opalescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected both in open vegetation and in forest borders, sometimes sympatric to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF9CE537D74BFACBD4B24142" baseAuthorityName="Myers" baseAuthorityYear="1942" box="[299,440,1305,1327]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Leptolebias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="155" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="splendens">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF9CE537D74BFACBD4B24142" box="[299,440,1305,1327]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">L. splendens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7A4D63FF9CE537D796FACBD7A84143" authorityName="Ladiges" authorityYear="1934" box="[502,674,1306,1327]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Cynopoecilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="155" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis id="B90EEAF2FF9CE537D796FACBD7A84143" box="[502,674,1306,1327]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="155">L. marmoratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
